  "texts": [
    "Since each such event is a cause of the events that follow it, it is natural to say that the man being able to provide these answers shows that he has a grasp of this underlying causal network and that his answers (A)-(E) are meant to pick out just these events in it.",
    "corresponds to the 'how?'",
    "in that the man pumping poison into the house understands that moving his arm in this way and in this context is a means to operate the pump, that operating the pump is a means to refill the cistern, and so on.",
    "If actions are events that might be picked out in this series or constructed from concatenations of such events, then to say that there is only one thing an agent does is to ask which of these is the action -it is \"to look for the fundamental description of what occurs […] and then think of intention as something, perhaps very complicated, which qualifies this\" (Anscombe, 2000, p. 29).",
    "But this is precisely what Anscombe thinks we shouldn't do."
  ],
